post_text:
#WeFinishStrong - This was not the year any of us planned on it being, but we are doing all we can to clear the path for our students to be successful!

Here are some options we have added to help our students earn their credit for this school year

1) Pathway for P (Passing Grades) Previously messaged - talk to your Success Coach.

2) Class Extensions with Support through June 4th - Incompletes will be given after June 4th. Our school calendar ends May 29th but students will have teacher support to complete their classes or earn P's through June 4th. Teachers will be available for support June 1 - 4th from 10:00 - 2:00.

3) Summer School for Credit Recovery from June 8th - 30th. Survey with more information will be sent out next week. Please focus now on finishing all your classes so you don't need credit recovery

Apply to Girls Who Codeâ€™s Virtual Summer Immersion Program for an unforgettable summer experience! During this FREE 2-week virtual program, you'll learn the computer science skills you need to make an impact, get an inside look into the tech field, and join a supportive lifelong sisterhood -- all while being virtually hosted by influential companies, like AT&T, Goldman Sachs, Disney, and more. Current 9th-11th grade girls and non-binary students are eligible to apply. SIP is 100% FREE and need-based stipends of up to $300 are available to help cover living and tech costs for those who qualify.

Applications are considered on a rolling basis, but classrooms are filling up fast! Apply today at girlswhocode.com/virtualsipform or learn more in a webinar.

March 14 at 10:44 AM Â·

Davis Tech is suspending all in-person courses from March 16-27 and moving to online instruction where possible.

Please visit www.davistech.edu for ongoing updates.

Participants get hands-on experience from construction professionals. Attendees will learn basic tool safety, architectural design, construction, electrical, heating and air conditioning, plumbing and more as they work on building a child's playhouse.

â„ï¸ Career Path High will conduct a late start, Monday morning, Feb. 3, 2020. â„ï¸ This means school will begin at 10:00. Davis Technical College is also closed until 10:00, so students will not be able to access the building before then.

Since your student's safety is of the utmost importance, if you choose to keep your student home tomorrow and they do their school work from home, they will not be marked absent. Teachers will be available at school and virtually between 10:00 - 4:00.

The National Weather Service has issued a Winter Storm Warning that will remain in effect from 10 p.m. this evening to 10 p.m. Monday. Forecasts call for total snow accumulations of 4-8 inches, with up to 14 inches on the benches.

In the event that weather worsens, the decision to cancel school will be made early in the morning. Updates will be emailed and posted on our social media pages

The teachers were up to their eyeballs in presents
From darling students and their thoughtful parents.

The sweaters were ugly and the weather was chilly

post_text:
Career Path High is an innovative model, early college High School in Kaysville, Utah. We are a tuition free, publicly funded charter school.

Our partnership with Davis Technical College provides our students with hands on learning opportunities in order to prepare them for their futures. We blend digital and in person instruction to provide students with the best support and learning opportunities.

We're committed to preparing each student for their future through dedicated mentorship and an early college experience.

Career Path High is a small school, and this nurturing environment helps us ensure student success. We are dedicated to preparing our graduates with the skills and confidence for their futures: whether that is entering their chosen career, continuing college, or both.

We invite you to join us and see how high school can and should be so much more.

Who is ready for a #FacultyFriday post!?

We are super thrilled to introduce our new art teacher Ms. Wagner!

Ms. Wagner was born and raised in West Valley City, Utah. She attended Westminster College, where she studied music and art. She completed her Master's in Secondary Education through Grand Canyon University. She has teaching experience both in Utah and in the state of Virginia as both a music and art instructor. This will be Ms. Wagner's first year with Career Path High as the fine arts instructor and is excited to be part of the team!

In her spare time, she enjoys hiking, skydiving, painting, drawing, and improv comedy clubs.

Thank you Ms. Wagner for being an amazing teacher and for being a part of Team CPH!

#careerpathhigh #bestteachersever #weloveourstaff

Get ready for Day 2 of our Suicide Prevention Week! We are so excited to be introducing our Semicolon Art Project and the SafeUT app today!

Safe_UT is an amazing app and crises line available to Utah's students. Students are able to communicate with a crises counselor and submit tips to their school. It is 100% Confidential.

Project Semicolon is an organization dedicated to providing support and awareness in order to save lives by preventing suicide.

â€œIn literature, an author uses a semicolon not to end a sentence, but to continue on. We see it as you are the author and your life is the sentence. Youâ€™re choosing to keep goingâ€ Amy Bleuel, creator of Project Semicolon

You can check out the resources this organization has for teens by going to: http://ow.ly/QO5B50w3LAC

#safeut #projectsemicolon #suicideispreventable #suicidepreventionweek #yourstoryisntover #suicidepreventionweek2019

We are honored to observe Suicide Prevention and Awareness Week at Career Path High. We hope that our activities and learning opportunities this week will help our students, families, and community be better prepared to recognize warning signs and feel empowered to know what resources are available.

Join us in Monday for a Mindfulness Session at 11:30 AM and Suicide Prevention Training with Davis County Health Department at 6PM. (Students who bring a parent to this training are eligible for 1 citizenship upgrade.)

#suicidepreventionweek2019 #mindfulness #qpr #thereishope #yourstoryisntoveryet #suicideispreventable #nationalsuicidepreventionweek #suicideprevention #suicidepreventionweek #suicidepreventionawareness #raiseawareness #chartersrock

post_text:
"I've got a fever, and the only perscription is more GONG!"

CPH students celebrate the successful completion of their classes and beginning of summer by striking the gong! Because of our flexible and blended model, our students can work at their own pace and finish their classes early! In fact, more than 1/3 of our senior class graduated early!

It is time for our last #TechTuesday post of the year, and we couldnâ€™t be more happier to celebrate Jesse, a graduating senior.

Jesse has successfully completed the Cyber Security program at Davis Technical College. He chose this program because computers and networking are some of his passions.

He really enjoyed his program. His favorite parts of the program were â€œlearning how computers work and how they talk to other computers.â€ He also loved the hands-on labs.

Jesse already had a great job in IT and plans on continue to work his way to the top.

Thank you, Jesse for being a great representative of our school! We are so proud of your success and look forward to seeing where your career will take you.

#cybersecurity #IT #ITCareers #careerready #earlycollege #beststudentsever #collegegrad #CTE #careereducation #blendedlearning

Computer Check-in -Thursday, May 30th

All computers are due to be checked in on the last day of school between 10 AM and 3 PM.

Please be sure to remove the computer case and clean both your computer and cord prior to check in.

Please be aware of the following:
- Computers and chargers are checked in at the same time. We will not check in computers without the charger.
- Students will be charged for any damage or loss to their computer and/or charger.

Questions about computer check-in? Please contact Mrs. Kobayashi: catherine.kobayashi@utahcph.org.

We are so thrilled to share another #TechTuesday post! Today we are excited to share Priscillaâ€™s story.

Priscilla studies Plumbing at Davis Technical College. She chose this program because of the high demand in the field and the incredible placement rate.

She loves how hands on her program is. She says, â€œThe first day I started I was learning how to weld, and the second day we were going out to a job site.â€

Priscilla dreams of becoming a master plumber and one day opening her own business.

Thank you, Priscilla for rocking it in your program and for the positive impact you have on our campus!

State Testing - 9th and 10th Graders

The State of Utah is launching a new state assessment this year, Utah Aspire Plus. This test uses ACT Aspire and Utah assessment questions.

We are excited for our students to take this new assessment as it will help us to better know how to help them be successful in high school and prepare them for college.

All 9th and 10th graders are required to participate. You can see the dates and times below.

All 9th Graders - May 8th and 15th 9:00 - 12:00
All 10th Graders - May 8th and 15th 12:30 - 3:30

We are looking for some awesome seniors to serve on our graduation committee! These students help plan our graduation banquet and ceremony.

This is a great opportunity for anyone who would like volunteer experience, has citizenship/attendance issues to resolve, or would like the opportunity to help create our best graduation celebration ever!

Interested? Contact Mr. Welch for the details: ryan.welch@utahcph.org.
